There was tension in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Abuja on Sunday when motorcycle riders, popularly known as ‘Okada’ stormed a popular estate in the metropolis. Findings revealed that the mayhem started when a hit-and-run driver rammed into some Okada riders in Kabusa area of the city, killing three of them in the process. The driver, according to an eyewitness, ran into Global Estate located after Sunnyvale in Kabusa, around Lokogoma, Abuja.   Train attack: Terrorists withdraw threat to kill 62 abducted…     Ex-Ebonyi SSG wins APGA Gov ticket     Izunaso, Mbata, Ndubueze get APC senatorial tickets in Imo   The angry Okada riders were said to have chased the driver to the estate, setting the gatehouse on fire. As of the time of filing this report, security operatives were said to have been drafted to the estate to prevent further destruction. Details Shortly…